  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal profile, COU omitted)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. The model is intended to predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5 operating at 2500 RPM and 5 L/min flow. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification was performed across all 13 ASME V&V 40 credibility factors. Seven factors were formally assessed; six remain flagged as epistemic gaps. All assessed factors achieved credibility levels meeting or exceeding required thresholds at MRL 5. Decision: Accepted. Note: the structured Context of Use block is carried only in this prose and in the bound requirement IRI; no machine-readable hasContextOfUse node is present.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/morrison-cou2-vad-mrl5-hemolysis",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/morrison-cou2-cfd-hemolysis-absolute-prediction",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/fda-centrifugal-pump-cfd-hemolysis-v3",
